article.headline: Winthrop 94, High Point 78
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- James Shuler scored 26 points and added 11 assists as Winthrop beat High Point 94-78 Thursday, to earn a shot at the Big South title. The win also placed Winthrop coach Gregg Marshall atop the schools' all-time win list with 161. "The record means that I have been very fortunate to have some excellent players and coaches during my eight seasons here at Winthrop," said Marshall, 42. Marshall needs 33 more victories to become the winningest coach in Big South history. Shuler was a perfect 18-of-18 from the free-throw line for the Eagles (19-7, 12-3), and Torrell Martin scored 17 for Winthrop. Akeem Scott scored a career-high 31, including six 3-pointers in the losing effort for High Point (14-12, 7-8). Winthrop's win ties the team with Birmingham-Southern atop the Big South standings. The Eagles and Panthers will play the regular season finale Saturday to see who wins the regular season title. That's important because the quarterfinals and finals in the conference tournament are hosted by the higher finisher in the regular season, and the semifinals will be held at the site of the regular-season champion.
